== SPICE related features ==

=== Summary ===
This pages describes the changes needed on oVirt to support new SPICE features in 3.1.

=== Background ===
Currently oVirt use the spicec client for remote Spice connections and RHEV adds the proprietary Incentives Pro USB redirector solution to add support for remote USB.
Since Fedora 16, the QEMU and Spice projects have added native support for USB remoting and are moving to a new client, virt-viewer, based on spice-gtk that includes more features and is based on a more portable code-base that will extend from Linux and Windows to more platforms in the future such as Mac OS. 
The virt-viewer client also includes support for the new native USB support in Spice.

