=== Detailed Description ===

==== New Spice Client ====

The Linux and Windows ''spicec'' based client will be replaced by the ''remote-viewer'' which is based on spice-gtk.
The ActiveX and spice-xpi packages will be updated to include the new client which is backwards compatible with spicec - allowing remote-viewer to be used for RHEV 3 based deployments as well as RHEV 3.1.


==== USB Support ====

For cluster level 3.1 (based on RHEL 6.3 support) native KVM/Spice USB redirection can be used in addition to the legacy Incentives Pro.


The current Incentives Pro solution needs to be supported for both 3.0 and 3.1 cluster levels.
''Note :''The native USB support in Spice and KVM currently does not support live migration.

*'''For 3.0 Cluster level'''
**Update New/Edit VM dialog to change USB text to “Legacy USB Support”
**Legacy USB Support field should be disabled for all Linux virtual machines
**Legacy USB support should allow selection only on Windows VMs but default to Off


*'''For 3.1 Cluster level'''
**Add checkbox for Enable USB support
***Checkbox should be unselected by default
**When checkbox is selected two radio buttons should be presented
***Legacy USB Support
***SPICE USB Support
**For Linux virtual machines Legacy USB Support should not be enabled


For both cluster 3.0 and 3.1 level USB should only be enabled if Spice is selected as remote protocol.

 
Documentation and online help should indicate that “Legacy USB support “is deprecated and will not be supported in future releases of RHEV.
When a user selects SPICE USB support we should present a warning that migration is NOT supported using SPICE USB redirection. 
